<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1924-11-11T22:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1924-11-11T22:00:00-05:00" n="359" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d359">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/5744: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Cunningham</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-11-12T11:00:00+08:00"><hi rend="italic">November 12,
                                        1924—11 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received November 12—3:20
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Following telegram has been received from Nanking: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“November 11, 5 p.m. Please send following telegram to the
                                    Department for me: ‘I have seen Marshal Chi today. He and
                                    Admiral Tu have sent vessel to meet Wu who is expected to arrive
                                    about the 13th for a conference. Chi has sent circular telegram
                                    supporting Tuan. Will accept Tuan’s leadership but not that of
                                    Feng or Chang. Invasion by the last two would be forcibly
                                    resisted.</p>
                                <p>Representatives of the governors of eight provinces now are
                                    assembling here to decide upon course of action.
                                Davis.’”</p></quote></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Cunningham</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>